events.description: Edward VI of England is crowned King of England at Westminster Abbey.
events.html: • 1547 – Edward VI of England is crowned King of England at Westminster Abbey.[4]

events.description: The Postal Service Act, establishing the United States Post Office Department, is signed by United States President George Washington.

events.description: Louis-Alexandre Berthier removes Pope Pius VI from power.
events.html: • 1798 – Louis-Alexandre Berthier removes Pope Pius VI from power.

events.description: Manuel Belgrano defeats the royalist army of Pío de Tristán during the Battle of Salta.
events.html: • 1813 – Manuel Belgrano defeats the royalist army of Pío de Tristán during the Battle of Salta.

events.description: Rossini's opera The Barber of Seville premieres at the Teatro Argentina in Rome.
events.html: • 1816 – Rossini's opera The Barber of Seville premieres at the Teatro Argentina in Rome.

events.description: William Buckland formally announces the name Megalosaurus, the first scientifically validly named non-avian dinosaur species.
events.html: • 1824 – William Buckland formally announces the name Megalosaurus, the first scientifically validly named non-avian dinosaur species.[5]

events.description: The 1835 Concepción earthquake destroys Concepción, Chile.
events.html: • 1835 – The 1835 Concepción earthquake destroys Concepción, Chile.

events.description: Polish insurgents lead an uprising in Kraków to incite a fight for national independence.
events.html: • 1846 – Polish insurgents lead an uprising in Kraków to incite a fight for national independence.

events.description: American Civil War: Battle of Olustee: The largest battle fought in Florida during the war.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: Battle of Olustee: The largest battle fought in Florida during the war.

events.description: End of the Uruguayan War, with a peace agreement between President Tomás Villalba and rebel leader Venancio Flores, setting the scene for the destructive War of the Triple Alliance.
events.html: • 1865 – End of the Uruguayan War, with a peace agreement between President Tomás Villalba and rebel leader Venancio Flores, setting the scene for the destructive War of the Triple Alliance.

events.description: The Metropolitan Museum of Art opens in New York City.

events.description: Tchaikovsky's ballet Swan Lake receives its premiere at the Bolshoi Theatre in Moscow.
events.html: • 1877 – Tchaikovsky's ballet Swan Lake receives its premiere at the Bolshoi Theatre in Moscow.

events.description: The legislature of Hawaii Territory convenes for the first time.
events.html: • 1901 – The legislature of Hawaii Territory convenes for the first time.

events.description: The U.S. Supreme Court upholds the constitutionality of Massachusetts's mandatory smallpox vaccination program in Jacobson v. Massachusetts.

events.description: Publication of the Futurist Manifesto in the French journal Le Figaro.

events.html: • 1913 – King O'Malley drives in the first survey peg to mark commencement of work on the construction of Canberra.

events.description: An earthquake kills between 114 and 130 in Georgia and heavily damages the town of Gori.
events.html: • 1920 – An earthquake kills between 114 and 130 in Georgia and heavily damages the town of Gori.

events.description: The U.S. Congress approves the construction of the San Francisco–Oakland Bay Bridge by the state of California.
events.html: • 1931 – The U.S. Congress approves the construction of the San Francisco–Oakland Bay Bridge by the state of California.

events.description: An anarchist uprising in Encarnación, Paraguay briefly transforms the city into a revolutionary commune.

events.description: Caroline Mikkelsen becomes the first woman to set foot in Antarctica.
events.html: • 1935 – Caroline Mikkelsen becomes the first woman to set foot in Antarctica.

events.description: The United States Merchant Marine Academy becomes a permanent Service Academy.
